defaultfinancing arrangements.
default The Commission’s recommendation was to devolve both domestic and non-domestic taxes to London and pass the responsibility for setting the tax rates and authority over all matters including revaluation
default, banding and discounts to the regional level of Government. 
defaultThe report also recommended 
defaultlifting
default 
defaultthe 
defaultGLA’s borrowing constraints. Such a reform would increase the number of alternative funding streams available to London and could provide sources of both f
defaultinancing and funding infrastructure projects without the need
default 
defaultfor central Government funding and 
defaultwith more reliance on the private sector.
